Let $\Omega$ be a bounded open interval, and let $p>1$ and
$q\in\left(0,p-1\right) $. Let $m\in L^{p^{\prime}}\left(\Omega\right) $ and
$0\leq c\in L^{\infty}\left(\Omega\right) $. We study existence of strictly
positive solutions for elliptic problems of the form $-\left(\left\|
u^{\prime}\right\|^{p-2}u^{\prime}\right) ^{\prime}+c\left(x\right)
u^{p-1}=m\left(x\right) u^{q}$ in $\Omega$, $u=0$ on $\partial\Omega$. We
mention that our results are new even in the case $c\equiv0$.